<aura:component extends="auradocs:topicPanel">
    <aura:set attribute="title" value="Using Tabs and Scrollers" />
    
    <h3><code>ui:tab</code></h3>
    <p><code>ui:tab</code> represents a tab, and multiple tabs are nested in a <code>ui:tabset</code> component. You can set the default tab by using <code>active="true"</code>.</p>
    <auradocs:info>See the <auradocs:defLink descriptor ="ui:tab">ui:tab</auradocs:defLink> component reference.</auradocs:info>
    <auradocs:example descriptor="auradocs:demoTab" />
    
    <h3><code>ui:scroller</code></h3>
    <p>Create a scrollable view using <code>ui:scroller</code>, which supports scroll bars and pull-to-refresh behaviors. You can set the width of the scroll area, and enable or disable vertical and horizontal scrolling.
     Shorter content leads to elastic scrolling.</p>
     <auradocs:info>See the <auradocs:defLink descriptor ="ui:scroller">ui:scroller</auradocs:defLink> component reference.</auradocs:info>
     <auradocs:example descriptor="auradocs:demoScroller" />

</aura:component>